addr="ring-0001"
title="Ring">Ring</fr:link>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda \in  R]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be a positive integer. A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Jordan Block</html:dfn> of size <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> with eigenvalue <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix which looks like
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {pmatrix} \lambda  &      1  &        &         &   \\         & \lambda  & \ddots  &         &   \\         &         & \ddots  &  1      &   \\         &         &        & \lambda  & 1 \\         &         &        &         & \lambda \end {pmatrix}.]]></fr:tex>
That is to say, the upper subdiagonal are all 1, the diagonal entries are all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda ]]></fr:tex>, and all other entries are zero.</fr:p>
 
   
